      "writtenOn": "2017-10-13T17:38:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "IMO think this is getting overly complicated, let me propose a design.\n\nthe combination of requirements\n1) make changes transactionally\n2) compare commits using urlfetch\n3) avoid urlfetch in transactions\nmake this tricky, but I think there is a way around it\n\nlet\u0027s fix the claim that StatusRevision never goes back. Then we can pretech history before the transaction\n\npseuducode (only to communicate the idea):\n\n  builder \u003d datastore.get(builderID)\n  if not builder:\n    with transaction:\n      builder \u003d datastore.get(builderID)\n      if builder \u003d\u003d nil:\n        log(\u0027registered new builder\u0027)\n        put(newBuilder(id, build.revision, build))\n        return\n\n  # builder is not nil\n  # it is either loaded with or without the transaction above\n\n  # history order is newest..oldest\n  history \u003d gitilesLog(builder.revision .. build.revision)\n  if len(history) \u003d\u003d 0:\n    log(build commit is old)\n    return\n  assert history[0] \u003d\u003d build.revision\n\n  with transaction:\n    builder \u003d datastore.get(builderID)\n    # builder cannot be nil\n    switch pos :\u003d history.index(builder.statusRevision); {\n    case pos \u003c 0:\n      # 1) builder.statusRevision never goes back, only forward\n      # 2) history contains commits up to build.revision\n      # \u003d\u003e builder has advanced beyond build.revision \n      log(build commit is old)\n      return\n\n    case pos \u003d\u003d 0 \u0026\u0026 build.createdTime \u003c builder.statusBuildTime:\n      log(build is out of order)\n      return\n    }\n\n    # * pos \u003d\u003d 0 and build is newer OR\n    # * pos \u003e 0 \u003d\u003e build commit is newer\n    # \u003d\u003e new state!\n    datastore.put(new_builder(id, build.revision, build))\n\nthis avoid thrashing because we can use commit history even if there was a change in the datastore and the overall amount of code might be smaller. IMO we don\u0027t need WithBuilder.\n\nWDYT?",
